<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Decide how the individual values should be sorted within the table. To do so, first activate one or several of the options <strong>Primary result</strong>, <strong>Scale basis</strong> or <strong>dimensions</strong>. Then, select one of the options <strong>Descending</strong> or <strong>Ascending</strong> for the previously selected options.<br>
<strong><em>Example:</em></strong> If you want to sort the entries according to the primary result of the key figure and the highest values should be displayed on top of the table, activate the option <strong>Primary result</strong> and then select the option <strong>Ascending</strong>.</p></td>
